  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Observational study of patients undergoing open heart surgery. During the procedure video
      clips of right heart are stored and compared to trans-oesophageal ultrasound recordings and
      ECG recordings.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Observational study of patients undergoing open heart surgery. During the procedure video
      clips of right heart are stored and compared to trans-oesophageal ultrasound recordings and
      ECG recordings. Right heart volume status and function is controlled and induced with
      theophylline and ventilator regulated positive end-expiratory pressure recordings.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
